== Code ==
<pre>{{Infobox Pokémon
|name    =
|image   =
|caption =
|number  =
|species =
|type    =
|move    =
|rarity  =
}}</pre>

== Usage ==
To use this template, place the code above at the top of an article and fill in the respective blanks.

'''Where:'''
*<code>name</code> should be filled with the name of the Pokémon.
*<code>image</code> should be filled with a full view of the Pokémon.
*<code>caption</code> should be filled with a description of the <code>image</code> spot.
*<code>number</code> should be filled with the National Pokédex number, i.e. Charizard is #006 (NOTE: The symbol "#" must not be added as it is already included in the template format).
*<code>species</code>species}}} should be filled with the species as listed in the Pokédex; i.e. Pikachu is the "Electric Mouse Pokémon" (NOTE: The word "Pokémon" must not be added as it is already included in the template format).
*<code>type</code> should be filled with type the Pokémon is classified. If there are two types, it should be put like this: "Type1/Type2".



